"title": "4293: water",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4293: water",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The colourless, odourless liquid that is essential for sustenance of life in human beings and animals. God is described as the spring of living water, being the source of life and salvation to those who come to him.</p>\n<h2>Water for drinking</h2>\n<h3>For human beings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:15-2Sam23:16\">2SA 23:15–23:16</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:17-1Chr11:18\">1CH 11:17–11:18</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:14-Gen21:19\">GEN 21:14–21:19</a> <em>God provides water for Hagar and Ishmael</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:22-Exod15:27\">EXO 15:22–15:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:1-Exod17:3\">EXO 17:1–17:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:1-Num20:11\">NUM 20:1–20:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut2:28\">DEU 2:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:19\">JDG 4:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:25\">JDG 5:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam30:11-1Sam30:12\">1SA 30:11–30:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:10\">1KI 17:10</a> <em>Elijah asks the widow at Zarephath for a drink of water</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:22\">2KI 6:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:25-2Chr18:26\">2CH 18:25–18:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:20\">NEH 9:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job6:19\">JOB 6:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:16\">ISA 33:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:8-Dan1:16\">DAN 1:8–1:16</a> <em>Daniel's resolve to live on vegetables and water</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:5\">HOS 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:42\">MAT 10:42</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:41\">MRK 9:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:7\">JHN 4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:23\">1TI 5:23</a></p>\n<h3>For animals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:9\">2KI 3:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:13-Gen24:19\">GEN 24:13–24:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:1-Gen29:10\">GEN 29:1–29:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:15-Exod2:16\">EXO 2:15–2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:3\">EXO 17:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:17\">2KI 3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:10-Ps104:11\">PSA 104:10–104:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:20\">ISA 43:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:15\">LUK 13:15</a></p>\n<h2>Water as a general descriptive term for liquid</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:25\">EXO 23:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:11\">1SA 25:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs13:6-1Kgs13:22\">1KI 13:6–13:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:4\">1KI 18:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job22:7\">JOB 22:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:21\">PRO 25:21</a></p>\n<h2>Abstention from water during fasting</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:9\">DEU 9:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:28\">EXO 34:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:18\">DEU 9:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:6\">EZR 10:6</a></p>\n<h2>Water for washing</h2>\n<h3>For general hygiene</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:4\">GEN 18:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:32\">GEN 24:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:24\">GEN 43:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:44\">LUK 7:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:1-John13:17\">JHN 13:1–13:17</a></p>\n<h3>For ritual cleansing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:15\">LEV 17:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:17-Exod30:21\">EXO 30:17–30:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:3-Lev1:9\">LEV 1:3–1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:20-Lev16:24\">LEV 16:20–16:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:7-Num19:9\">NUM 19:7–19:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:6\">JHN 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:22\">HEB 10:22</a></p>\n<h2>Water for cooking</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:9-Exod12:10\">EXO 12:9–12:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek24:3-Ezek24:5\">EZK 24:3–24:5</a></p>\n<h2>Rainwater</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:4\">JDG 5:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:11-Gen7:12\">GEN 7:11–7:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:10\">JOB 5:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job37:13\">JOB 37:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:25-Job38:28\">JOB 38:25–38:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:37\">JOB 38:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:17\">PSA 77:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl11:3\">ECC 11:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:3\">HOS 6:3</a></p>\n<h2>Sources and stores of water</h2>\n<h3>Wells</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:19-Gen26:20\">GEN 26:19–26:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:19\">GEN 21:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:11\">GEN 24:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:25\">ISA 37:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:6\">JHN 4:6</a></p>\n<h3>Springs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:11-Jas3:12\">JAS 3:11–3:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:15-Josh15:19\">JOS 15:15–15:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:11-Judg1:15\">JDG 1:11–1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:10-Rev8:11\">REV 8:10–8:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:7\">REV 14:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:4\">REV 16:4</a></p>\n<h3>Cisterns</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:13\">JER 2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:36\">LEV 11:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:31\">2KI 18:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:16\">ISA 36:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov5:15-Prov5:16\">PRO 5:15–5:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer14:3\">JER 14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:6\">JER 38:6</a></p>\n<h2>Abundance of water as a sign of blessing</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:7\">DEU 8:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num24:7\">NUM 24:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:7\">DEU 10:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:1-Ps1:3\">PSA 1:1–1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:7-Jer17:8\">JER 17:7–17:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:5-Ezek17:6\">EZK 17:5–17:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek19:10-Ezek19:11\">EZK 19:10–19:11</a></p>\n<h2>Baptism in water</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:11\">MAT 3:11</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:8\">MRK 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:16\">LUK 3:16</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:13-Matt3:17\">MAT 3:13–3:17</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:9-Mark1:11\">MRK 1:9–1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:21-Luke3:22\">LUK 3:21–3:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:31-John1:34\">JHN 1:31–1:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:26-John1:27\">JHN 1:26–1:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:23\">JHN 3:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:5\">ACT 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:36-Acts8:39\">ACT 8:36–8:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:47\">ACT 10:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:16\">ACT 11:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:20-1Pet3:22\">1PE 3:20–3:22</a></p>\n<h2>Living water</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:13\">JER 17:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:8-Zech14:9\">ZEC 14:8–14:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:4-John4:26\">JHN 4:4–4:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:37-John7:39\">JHN 7:37–7:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:13-Rev7:17\">REV 7:13–7:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:6-Rev21:8\">REV 21:6–21:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:1-Rev22:2\">REV 22:1–22:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:17\">REV 22:17</a></p>\n<h2>Metaphorical references to water</h2>\n<h3>As a symbol of affliction</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:17\">2SA 22:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:1\">PSA 69:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:20\">ISA 30:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:2\">ISA 43:2</a></p>\n<h3>As a symbol of salvation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa12:3\">ISA 12:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:10\">ISA 49:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:1\">ISA 55:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:25\">EZK 36:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:38\">JHN 7:38</a></p>\n<h3>As a symbol of life</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:14\">JHN 4:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:37-John7:39\">JHN 7:37–7:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:6\">REV 21:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:17\">REV 22:17</a></p>\n<h3>Other metaphorical references</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:15\">SNG 4:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:20\">ISA 30:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:6\">ISA 35:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:12\">ISA 44:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:1\">JER 9:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25-Eph5:26\">EPH 5:25–5:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:17\">2PE 2:17</a></p>",
